results.title: Jump Space Early Access Video Review
creator: IGN Middle East
results.description: Jump Space reviewed in Early Access by Will Borgor on PC, also available on Xbox.After completing Jump Space’s first early access chapter, trying out both of its ships, and spending around 15 hours traveling the stars, I quite like what’s here – even if, like your starting ship, it’s still under construction. It’s best enjoyed with a group because co-op games almost always are, but also because there are plenty of relatively quiet moments where it’s basically a chill chat room in space. There are some parts of this ship that need a little TLC, but I’d be lying if I said I wasn’t nearly always having fun playing it. Even when things seem all but lost and everything’s on fire, you can still pull it out if you and your crew work together, play smart, and get a little lucky. Even though there’s still work to do to get Jump Space shipshape, particularly when it comes to adding more variety to its mission objectives, it’s already proven its concept is a winner.

results.description: United Nations investigators on Tuesday unveiled rampant and systemic corruption by South Sudan’s ruling class, compounding the country’s security challenges and putting the pivotal oil-driven economy at severe risk. The global agency has accused South Sudanese authorities of plundering the country’s wealth, including bogus payments totaling $1.7 billion in the 2021-2024 period to companies linked with Vice President Benjamin Bol Mel for road construction contracts that were never delivered.
